{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897900116,"sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc36de5001R2QkDbDOzJj4sq","messageID":"msg_d7bc361990013fLYSD85PJds6n","sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9829d199cd8742229f1b3ee8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 单元测试 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers comprehensive Python unit tests for the `agentcube-sdk` package (`sdk-python/`). The SDK provides high-level Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 Scope\n10: \n11: | Module | File | Lines | Test File | Status |\n12: |--------|------|-------|-----------|--------|\n13: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` | 161 | `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | **Partial** — 635 lines, but 3 methods missing `test_` prefix (won't run) |\n14: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` | 79 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** — 837 lines |\n15: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` | 96 | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **Good** — 370 lines |\n16: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | 176 | `tests/test_data_plane.py` | **Good** — 641 lines |\n17: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 80 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** |\n18: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes | 21 | `tests/test_exceptions.py` | **Good** — 77 lines |\n19: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` | 14 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Good** |\n20: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` | 7 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing edge cases |\n21: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` | 17 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing handler reuse test |\n22: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports | 5 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** — 55 lines |\n23: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Client re-exports | 6 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** |\n24: \n25: ### 1.3 System Context\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                        Python SDK (agentcube)                        │\n30: │                                                                       │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     │\n32: │  │  CodeInterpreterClient│     │     AgentRuntimeClient        │     │\n33: │  │  (high-level facade)  │     │   (high-level facade)         │     │\n34: │  └───────┬──────────────┘     └──────────┬────────────────────┘     │\n35: │          │                               │                           │\n36: │  ┌───────▼──────────────┐     ┌──────────▼────────────────────┐     │\n37: │  │  ControlPlaneClient  │     │  AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  │     │\n38: │  │  (Workload Manager)  │     │   (Router — Agent Runtime)    │     │\n39: │  └──────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     │\n40: │          │                                                       │\n41: │  ┌───────▼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n42: │  │           CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient                      │  │\n43: │  │              (Router — Code Interpreter)                      │  │\n44: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n45: │                                                                       │\n46: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n47: │  │                    Utilities                                   │  │\n48: │  │  create_session  │  read_token_from_file  │  get_logger       │  │\n49: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n50: │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n51: │  │                   Exceptions                                   │  │\n52: │  │  AgentCubeError → CommandExecutionError                       │  │\n53: │  │                 → SessionError                                │  │\n54: │  │                 → DataPlaneError                              │  │\n55: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n56: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n57:          │                                              │\n58:          ▼                                              ▼\n59: ┌──────────────────┐                        ┌──────────────────────┐\n60: │  Workload Manager│                        │      Router           │\n61: │  (Control Plane) │                        │  (Data Plane)         │\n62: │  K8s API Server  │                        │  HTTP proxy to pods   │\n63: └──────────────────┘                        └──────────────────────┘\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### 1.4 Design Principles\n67: \n68: - **Mock at the boundary**: All HTTP calls are mocked via `MagicMock` on `session.post/get/delete/request`. No real network calls.\n69: - **`unittest.mock.patch`**: Used for class-level and function-level patching. Consistent with existing test patterns.\n70: - **Environment isolation**: Tests that depend on env vars use `patch.dict(os.environ, ...)` with `clear=True`.\n71: - **Resource cleanup**: Every test that creates a client calls `client.close()` or `client.stop()` to release HTTP sessions.\n72: - **Table-driven patterns**: Where applicable (e.g., language aliases, timeout variants), use parameterized approaches.\n73: \n74: ### 1.5 Package Structure (test files)\n75: \n76: ```\n77: python-sdk/tests/\n78: ├── __init__.py                          # Package marker\n79: ├── conftest.py                          # Shared fixtures (mock_requests_session, mock_create_session)\n80: ├── test_imports.py                      # Package import and __all__ verification\n81: ├── test_exceptions.py                   # Exception hierarchy tests\n82: ├── test_utils.py                        # Utility function tests (http, utils, log)\n83: ├── test_control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient tests\n84: ├── test_data_plane.py                   # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient tests\n85: ├── test_code_interpreter.py             # CodeInterpreterClient tests\n86: ├── test_agent_runtime.py                # AgentRuntimeClient + AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient tests\n87: └── test_integration.py                  # NEW — cross-component integration tests\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### 1.6 Dependencies\n91: \n92: | Dependency | Version | Test Use |\n93: |------------|---------|----------|\n94: | `pytest` | ≥8.0 | Test runner, fixtures, parametrize |\n95: | `requests` | any | HTTP client (mocked) |\n96: | `PyJWT` | ≥2.0.0 | SDK dependency (not directly tested) |\n97: | `cryptography` | any | SDK dependency (not directly tested) |\n98: | `unittest.mock` | stdlib | MagicMock, patch, patch.dict |\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 2. Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### 2.1 Mock Objects Required\n105: \n106: #### `mock_http_response` (requests.Response)\n107: \n108: Standard mock for HTTP responses across all client tests:\n109: \n110: ```python\n111: mock_resp = MagicMock(spec=requests.Response)\n112: mock_resp.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}\n113: mock_resp.status_code = 200\n114: mock_resp.raise_for_status = MagicMock()\n115: mock_resp.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-1\"}\n116: mock_resp.iter_content.return_value = [b\"chunk1\", b\"chunk2\"]\n117: ```\n118: \n119: #### `mock_session` (requests.Session)\n120: \n121: Used when testing session-level behavior:\n122: \n123: ```python\n124: mock_session = MagicMock()\n125: mock_session.post.return_value = mock_resp\n126: mock_session.get.return_value = mock_resp\n127: mock_session.delete.return_value = mock_resp\n128: mock_session.request.return_value = mock_resp\n129: mock_session.headers = {}\n130: mock_session.adapters = {\"http://\": adapter, \"https://\": adapter}\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### 2.2 Test Fixtures\n134: \n135: #### CodeInterpreterClient fixture\n136: \n137: ```python\n138: def make_ci_client(session_id=\"sess-1\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\", **kwargs):\n139:     \"\"\"Create a CodeInterpreterClient with mocked dependencies.\"\"\"\n140:     with patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\") as mock_cp, \\\n141:          patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n142:         mock_cp.return_value = MagicMock()\n143:         mock_dp.return_value = MagicMock()\n144:         client = CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=session_id, router_url=router_url, **kwargs)\n145:         yield client, mock_cp, mock_dp\n146:         client.stop()\n147: ```\n148: \n149: #### AgentRuntimeClient fixture\n150: \n151: ```python\n152: def make_ar_client(session_id=\"sess-1\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\", **kwargs):\n153:     \"\"\"Create an AgentRuntimeClient with mocked dependencies.\"\"\"\n154:     with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n155:         mock_dp.return_value = MagicMock()\n156:         mock_dp.return_value.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = session_id\n157:         client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=router_url, **kwargs)\n158:         yield client, mock_dp\n159:         client.close()\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### 2.2 Key Class Signatures\n163: \n164: #### CodeInterpreterClient\n165: \n166: | Method | Signature | Delegates To |\n167: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n168: | `__init__` | `(name, namespace, ttl, workload_manager_url, router_url, auth_token, verbose, session_id)` | ControlPlaneClient + CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n169: | `_init_data_plane` | `() -> None` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name) |\n170: | `__enter__` | `() -> self` | — |\n171: | `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | `stop()` |\n172: | `stop` | `() -> None` | dp_client.close(), cp_client.delete_session(), cp_client.close() |\n173: | `execute_command` | `(command: str, timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | dp_client.execute_command([command], timeout+2.0) |\n174: | `run_code` | `(language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | write_file() + execute_command() |\n175: | `write_file` | `(content: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.write_file() |\n176: | `upload_file` | `(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.upload_file() |\n177: | `download_file` | `(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.download_file() |\n178: | `list_files` | `(path: str=\".\") -> Any` | dp_client.list_files() |\n179: \n180: #### ControlPlaneClient\n181: \n182: | Method | Signature | HTTP |\n183: |--------|-----------|------|\n184: | `__init__` | `(workload_manager_url, auth_token, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session with headers |\n185: | `create_session` | `(name, namespace, metadata, ttl) -> str` | POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` |\n186: | `delete_session` | `(session_id: str) -> bool` | DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` |\n187: | `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n188: \n189: #### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n190: \n191: | Method | Signature | HTTP |\n192: |--------|-----------|------|\n193: | `__init__` | `(session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name, base_url, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session with `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n194: | `_request` | `(method, endpoint, body, **kwargs) -> Response` | `{base_url}{endpoint}` |\n195: | `execute_command` | `(command: Union[str, List], timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | POST `api/execute` |\n196: | `run_code` | `(language, code, timeout) -> str` | write_file + execute_command |\n197: | `write_file` | `(content, remote_path) -> None` | POST `api/files` (JSON, base64) |\n198: | `upload_file` | `(local_path, remote_path) -> None` | POST `api/files` (multipart) |\n199: | `download_file` | `(remote_path, local_path) -> None` | GET `api/files/{clean_path}` (stream) |\n200: | `list_files` | `(path=\".\") -> Any` | GET `api/files?path={path}` |\n201: | `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n202: \n203: #### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n204: \n205: | Method | Signature | HTTP |\n206: |--------|-----------|------|\n207: | `__init__` | `(router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session |\n208: | `bootstrap_session_id` | `() -> str` | GET `{base_url}` → reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n209: | `invoke` | `(session_id, payload, timeout) -> Response` | POST `{base_url}` with JSON + session header |\n210: | `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n211: \n212: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n213: \n214: | Method | Signature | Delegates To |\n215: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n216: | `__init__` | `(agent_name, namespace, router_url, verbose, session_id, timeout, connect_timeout)` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient + bootstrap |\n217: | `__enter__` | `() -> self` | — |\n218: | `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | `close()` |\n219: | `invoke` | `(payload: Dict, timeout: Optional[float]) -> Any` | dp_client.invoke() → resp.json() |\n220: | `close` | `() -> None` | dp_client.close() |\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ## 3. API Contracts\n225: \n226: ### 3.1 CodeInterpreterClient Contracts\n227: \n228: #### Initialization\n229: \n230: | Scenario | Condition | Result |\n231: |----------|-----------|--------|\n232: | No session_id provided | `session_id=None` | Calls `cp_client.create_session()`, sets `self.session_id`, sets `_session_created=True` |\n233: | Session_id provided | `session_id=\"existing\"` | Skips create_session, sets `_session_created=False` |\n234: | Router URL from arg | `router_url=\"http://x\"` | Uses provided URL |\n235: | Router URL from env | `router_url=None`, `ROUTER_URL=\"http://x\"` | Uses env var |\n236: | Router URL missing | Neither arg nor env | Raises `ValueError(\"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL env var must be set\")` |\n237: \n238: #### Data Plane Init Failure\n239: \n240: | Scenario | `_session_created` | `session_id` | Result |\n241: |----------|-------------------|-------------|--------|\n242: | DP init fails, session was created | True | non-None | Logs warning, calls `delete_session(session_id)`, sets `session_id=None`, re-raises |\n243: | DP init fails, session was reused | False | non-None | Re-raises without cleanup (caller owns session) |\n244: \n245: #### Context Manager\n246: \n247: | Scenario | Result |\n248: |----------|--------|\n249: | `__enter__` | Returns `self` |\n250: | `__exit__` (no exception) | Calls `stop()` |\n251: | `__exit__` (with exception) | Calls `stop()`, returns `None` (does not suppress) |\n252: \n253: #### stop()\n254: \n255: | Condition | Action |\n256: |-----------|--------|\n257: | `dp_client` exists and not None | `dp_client.close()`, set to `None` |\n258: | `session_id` is not None | `cp_client.delete_session(session_id)`, set to `None` |\n259: | `cp_client` exists and not None | `cp_client.close()`, set to `None` |\n260: | Called multiple times | Idempotent — no-op after first call |\n261: \n262: #### execute_command\n263: \n264: | Input | Transformation | DP Call |\n265: |-------|---------------|---------|\n266: | `\"echo hello\"` (string) | → `[\"echo hello\"]` | `dp.execute_command([\"echo hello\"], timeout=read_timeout)` |\n267: | `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (list) | → `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (as-is) | `dp.execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\"], timeout=read_timeout)` |\n268: | `timeout=None` | → `timeout_value=120`, `read_timeout=122.0` | DP call with `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n269: | `timeout=10.0` | → `timeout_value=10.0`, `read_timeout=12.0` | DP call with `(connect_timeout, 12.0)` |\n270: \n271: #### run_code\n272: \n273: | Language | Action |\n274: |----------|--------|\n275: | `\"python\"`, `\"py\"`, `\"python3\"` (case-insensitive) | Write timestamped `.py` file, execute `python3 <file>` |\n276: | Any other | Raises `ValueError(\"Unsupported language: {language}\")` |\n277: \n278: ### 3.2 ControlPlaneClient Contracts\n279: \n280: #### Initialization\n281: \n282: | Condition | Result |\n283: |-----------|--------|\n284: | `workload_manager_url` provided | `base_url = workload_manager_url` |\n285: | `workload_manager_url=None`, env set | `base_url = WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` |\n286: | Neither provided | Raises `ValueError(\"workload_manager_url must be provided or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var must be set\")` |\n287: | `auth_token` provided | `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header set |\n288: | `auth_token=None`, SA file exists | Token read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n289: | `auth_token=None`, SA file missing | No Authorization header set |\n290: | `auth_token=\"\"` (empty string) | No Authorization header set (falsy check) |\n291: \n292: #### create_session\n293: \n294: | HTTP | Request | Response |\n295: |------|---------|----------|\n296: | POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON: `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | Returns `data[\"sessionId\"]` |\n297: | Timeout | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` | — |\n298: | Missing sessionId in response | — | Raises `ValueError(\"Response missing 'sessionId' field\")` |\n299: | HTTP error | — | `resp.raise_for_status()` propagates |\n300: \n301: #### delete_session\n302: \n303: | HTTP Status | Result |\n304: |-------------|--------|\n305: | 2xx | Returns `True` |\n306: | 404 | Returns `True` (idempotent) |\n307: | Other error (HTTPError, ConnectionError, Timeout) | Logs warning, returns `False` |\n308: \n309: ### 3.3 CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Contracts\n310: \n311: #### Base URL Construction\n312: \n313: | Condition | Result |\n314: |-----------|--------|\n315: | `base_url` provided | `self.base_url = base_url` (ignores router_url/namespace/cr_name) |\n316: | `base_url=None` | `self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` |\n317: \n318: #### execute_command\n319: \n320: | Input | Body | Timeout |\n321: |-------|------|---------|\n322: | `\"sleep 10\"`, `timeout=10.0` | `{\"command\": [\"sleep\", \"10\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 12.0)` |\n323: | `\"ls\"`, `timeout=None` | `{\"command\": [\"ls\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n324: | `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (list) | `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n325: \n326: | Response | Result |\n327: |----------|--------|\n328: | `{\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"ok\"}` | Returns `\"ok\"` |\n329: | `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"err\"}` | Raises `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"err\", command=[...])` |\n330: \n331: #### write_file\n332: \n333: | Input | Body |\n334: |-------|------|\n335: | `\"hello\"`, `/tmp/test.txt` | `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": base64(\"hello\"), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n336: \n337: #### upload_file\n338: \n339: | Input | Multipart |\n340: |-------|-----------|\n341: | `/local/file.txt`, `/remote/file.txt` | `files={'file': ('file.txt', f)}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, headers include `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n342: \n343: #### download_file\n344: \n345: | Input | URL |\n346: |-------|-----|\n347: | `/remote/path.txt`, `/local/out.txt` | GET `{base_url}api/files/remote/path.txt` (leading `/` stripped) |\n348: \n349: ### 3.4 AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Contracts\n350: \n351: #### bootstrap_session_id\n352: \n353: | Response Header | Result |\n354: |-----------------|--------|\n355: | `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123` | Returns `\"abc-123\"` |\n356: | Missing header | Raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` |\n357: | HTTP error | `raise_for_status()` propagates |\n358: \n359: #### invoke\n360: \n361: | Input | Headers | Timeout |\n362: |-------|---------|---------|\n363: | `session_id=\"s1\"`, `payload={}`, `timeout=None` | `{\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"s1\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}` | `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n364: | `timeout=30.0` | Same | `(connect_timeout, 30.0)` |\n365: \n366: ### 3.5 Utility Contracts\n367: \n368: #### create_session\n369: \n370: | Input | Result |\n371: |-------|--------|\n372: | `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` (defaults) | Session with HTTPAdapter mounted on `http://` and `https://` |\n373: | Custom values | Session with custom pool settings |\n374: \n375: #### read_token_from_file\n376: \n377: | Condition | Result |\n378: |-----------|--------|\n379: | File exists with `\"token\\n\"` | Returns `\"token\"` (stripped) |\n380: | File exists with `\"  token  \\n\"` | Returns `\"token\"` (stripped) |\n381: | File not found | Returns `\"\"` |\n382: \n383: #### get_logger\n384: \n385: | Condition | Result |\n386: |-----------|--------|\n387: | First call with name `\"x\"` | Creates logger, adds StreamHandler with formatter |\n388: | Second call with same name `\"x\"` | Returns existing logger (no duplicate handlers) |\n389: | `level=logging.DEBUG` | Logger level = 10 |\n390: | `level=\"DEBUG\"` | Logger level = 10 |\n391: | `level=logging.INFO` (default) | Logger level = 20 |\n392: \n393: ---\n394: \n395: ## 4. Error Handling\n396: \n397: ### 4.1 Error Classification\n398: \n399: | Component | Error Source | Test Strategy |\n400: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n401: | ControlPlaneClient | `create_session` HTTP error | Mock `session.post` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n402: | ControlPlaneClient | `delete_session` network error | Mock `session.delete` with `RequestException` side_effect |\n403: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `execute_command` non-zero exit | Mock response JSON with `exit_code != 0` |\n404: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | Any HTTP error | Mock `session.request` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n405: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `bootstrap_session_id` missing header | Mock response with empty headers dict |\n406: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `invoke` HTTP error | Mock `session.post` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n407: | CodeInterpreterClient | DP init failure | Mock `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` constructor to raise |\n408: | CodeInterpreterClient | Router URL missing | Patch env, assert `ValueError` |\n409: | AgentRuntimeClient | Session not initialized | Mock bootstrap to return `None` or `\"\"` |\n410: \n411: ### 4.2 Exception Hierarchy\n412: \n413: ```\n414: Exception\n415: └── AgentCubeError (base)\n416:     ├── CommandExecutionError (exit_code, stderr, command)\n417:     ├── SessionError (docstring only, not raised by core)\n418:     └── DataPlaneError (docstring only, not raised by core)\n419: ```\n420: \n421: Tests verify:\n422: - `issubclass(CommandExecutionError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n423: - `issubclass(SessionError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n424: - `issubclass(DataPlaneError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n425: - `CommandExecutionError` attributes: `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`\n426: - `CommandExecutionError` message format: `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n427: \n428: ---\n429: \n430: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n431: \n432: ### 5.1 Test Categories\n433: \n434: | Category | Scope | Files |\n435: |----------|-------|-------|\n436: | Import/export tests | Package structure, `__all__` | `test_imports.py` |\n437: | Exception tests | Hierarchy, attributes, messages | `test_exceptions.py` |\n438: | Utility tests | Pure functions, no side effects | `test_utils.py` |\n439: | Control plane tests | HTTP client, session lifecycle | `test_control_plane.py` |\n440: | Data plane tests (CI) | HTTP client, file ops, execute | `test_data_plane.py` |\n441: | Data plane tests (AR) | HTTP client, bootstrap, invoke | `test_agent_runtime.py` |\n442: | High-level CI client | Facade, lifecycle, delegation | `test_code_interpreter.py` |\n443: | High-level AR client | Facade, lifecycle, delegation | `test_agent_runtime.py` |\n444: | Integration tests | Cross-component, end-to-end flows | `test_integration.py` (NEW) |\n445: \n446: ### 5.2 Bug Fixes Required (Existing Tests)\n447: \n448: #### `test_code_interpreter.py` — Missing `test_` prefix\n449: \n450: Three methods in `TestStop` class are named without `test_` prefix and will NOT be discovered by pytest:\n451: \n452: | Current Name | Required Name |\n453: |--------------|---------------|\n454: | `stop_closes_dp_client` | `test_stop_closes_dp_client` |\n455: | `stop_deletes_session` | `test_stop_deletes_session` |\n456: | `stop_closes_cp_client` | `test_stop_closes_cp_client` |\n457: \n458: ### 5.3 Detailed Test Plan — New/Additional Tests\n459: \n460: #### `test_code_interpreter.py` — Additional Tests\n461: \n462: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n463: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n464: | 1 | `test_stop_when_session_id_is_none` | stop | session_id=None → skips delete_session, still closes dp and cp |\n465: | 2 | `test_stop_when_dp_client_not_initialized` | stop | No dp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr check) |\n466: | 3 | `test_stop_when_cp_client_not_initialized` | stop | No cp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr check) |\n467: | 4 | `test_run_code_python3_language` | run_code | `\"python3\"` → writes file + executes |\n468: | 5 | `test_run_code_py_language` | run_code | `\"py\"` → writes file + executes |\n469: | 6 | `test_run_code_case_insensitive` | run_code | `\"PYTHON\"` → writes file + executes |\n470: | 7 | `test_run_code_passes_timeout_to_execute` | run_code | `timeout=30.0` → passed through to execute_command |\n471: | 8 | `test_execute_command_with_list_input` | execute_command | `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` → passed as-is to dp (not double-wrapped) |\n472: | 9 | `test_execute_command_empty_string` | execute_command | `\"\"` → `[\"\"]` sent to dp |\n473: | 10 | `test_session_created_flag_true_when_no_session_id` | __init__ | `_session_created=True` when session_id=None |\n474: | 11 | `test_session_created_flag_false_when_session_id_provided` | __init__ | `_session_created=False` when session_id provided |\n475: | 12 | `test_logger_name_is_correct` | __init__ | `logger.name == \"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` |\n476: | 13 | `test_data_plane_init_called_with_correct_params` | _init_data_plane | session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name passed correctly |\n477: \n478: #### `test_data_plane.py` — Additional Tests\n479: \n480: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n481: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n482: | 1 | `test_execute_command_http_error_propagates` | execute_command | HTTP 500 → raise_for_status propagates HTTPError |\n483: | 2 | `test_write_file_http_error_propagates` | write_file | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n484: | 3 | `test_write_file_unicode_content` | write_file | Unicode string → base64 encoded correctly |\n485: | 4 | `test_upload_file_nonexistent_raises_io_error` | upload_file | File not found → FileNotFoundError propagates |\n486: | 5 | `test_upload_file_http_error_propagates` | upload_file | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n487: | 6 | `test_download_file_creates_local_file` | download_file | Verifies file content written correctly |\n488: | 7 | `test_list_files_http_error_propagates` | list_files | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n489: | 8 | `test_run_code_delegates_to_write_and_execute` | run_code | Full delegation path verified |\n490: | 9 | `test_request_default_timeout_tuple` | _request | No timeout override → `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n491: | 10 | `test_request_custom_timeout_override` | _request | timeout kwarg → used instead of default |\n492: \n493: #### `test_control_plane.py` — Additional Tests\n494: \n495: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n496: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n497: | 1 | `test_create_session_with_none_metadata` | create_session | `metadata=None` → body includes `\"metadata\": null` |\n498: | 2 | `test_create_session_url_with_trailing_slash` | create_session | base_url with trailing slash → URL constructed correctly |\n499: | 3 | `test_delete_session_url_construction` | delete_session | Verifies exact URL format |\n500: | 4 | `test_session_headers_content_type_always_set` | __init__ | Content-Type always `application/json` |\n501: | 5 | `test_auth_token_empty_string_no_header` | __init__ | `auth_token=\"\"` → no Authorization header |\n502: \n503: #### `test_agent_runtime.py` — Additional Tests\n504: \n505: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n506: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n507: | 1 | `test_invoke_http_error_propagates` | invoke (DP) | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n508: | 2 | `test_invoke_with_empty_payload` | invoke (DP) | `{}` → valid POST |\n509: | 3 | `test_bootstrap_session_id_empty_string_treated_as_missing` | bootstrap_session_id | Header value `\"\"` → raises ValueError |\n510: | 4 | `test_close_delegates_to_session_close` | close (DP) | Verifies session.close() called |\n511: \n512: #### `test_utils.py` — Additional Tests\n513: \n514: | # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n515: |---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n516: | 1 | `test_read_token_from_file_empty_file` | read_token_from_file | Empty file → returns `\"\"` |\n517: | 2 | `test_read_token_from_file_multiline_strips` | read_token_from_file | `\"token\\n\\n\"` → returns `\"token\"` |\n518: | 3 | `test_get_logger_handler_not_duplicated` | get_logger | Second call with same name → only 1 handler |\n519: | 4 | `test_get_logger_formatter_is_set` | get_logger | Handler has Formatter with correct format string |\n520: | 5 | `test_get_logger_handler_is_stream_handler` | get_logger | Handler type is StreamHandler |\n521: | 6 | `test_create_session_independent_instances` | create_session | Two calls → two independent Session objects |\n522: \n523: #### `test_integration.py` — NEW File\n524: \n525: | # | Test Name | Components | Description |\n526: |---|-----------|------------|-------------|\n527: | 1 | `test_ci_full_lifecycle_create_execute_stop` | CI Client + CP + DP | Create session → execute command → stop (full flow with all mocks) |\n528: | 2 | `test_ci_context_manager_with_exception` | CI Client + CP + DP | Exception in context block → stop still called |\n529: | 3 | `test_ci_pre_provisioned_session_no_control_plane_calls` | CI Client + CP | session_id provided → no create_session call |\n530: | 4 | `test_ci_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` | CI Client + CP + DP | DP init fails → session deleted, exception re-raised |\n531: | 5 | `test_ar_full_lifecycle_bootstrap_invoke_close` | AR Client + DP | Bootstrap session → invoke → close (full flow) |\n532: | 6 | `test_ar_context_manager_with_exception` | AR Client + DP | Exception in context block → close still called |\n533: | 7 | `test_ar_pre_provisioned_session_no_bootstrap` | AR Client + DP | session_id provided → no bootstrap call |\n534: | 8 | `test_ar_missing_session_id_invoke_raises` | AR Client + DP | Bootstrap returns None → invoke raises ValueError |\n535: | 9 | `test_ci_execute_command_timeout_propagation` | CI Client + DP | Custom timeout → +2.0 buffer → DP receives correct value |\n536: | 10 | `test_ar_invoke_timeout_propagation` | AR Client + DP | Custom timeout → DP receives correct value |\n537: | 11 | `test_ci_run_code_python_writes_and_executes` | CI Client + DP | run_code(\"python\", ...) → write_file + execute_command |\n538: | 12 | `test_ci_run_code_unsupported_language` | CI Client | run_code(\"ruby\", ...) → ValueError |\n539: | 13 | `test_ci_file_operations_delegation` | CI Client + DP | write/upload/download/list all delegate to DP |\n540: | 14 | `test_cp_create_and_delete_session_flow` | CP Client | create_session → delete_session → verify URLs and methods |\n541: | 15 | `test_dp_execute_command_exit_code_error` | CI DP Client | Non-zero exit → CommandExecutionError raised |\n542: | 16 | `test_env_var_precedence_router_url` | CI Client | Arg takes precedence over ROUTER_URL env var |\n543: | 17 | `test_env_var_precedence_workload_manager_url` | CP Client | Arg takes precedence over WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var |\n544: | 18 | `test_ci_stop_idempotent` | CI Client | Multiple stop() calls → each cleanup action called exactly once |\n545: | 19 | `test_ar_close_idempotent` | AR Client | Multiple close() calls → dp_client.close called each time |\n546: | 20 | `test_ci_session_created_flag_behavior` | CI Client | _session_created=True → cleanup on DP failure; False → no cleanup |\n547: \n548: ### 5.4 Mocking Strategy\n549: \n550: | Dependency | Mock Approach | Rationale |\n551: |-----------|---------------|-----------|\n552: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\")` | Isolates CI client from control plane |\n553: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\")` | Isolates CI client from data plane |\n554: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\")` | Isolates AR client from data plane |\n555: | `requests.Session` methods | `client.session.post = MagicMock(...)` | Direct method replacement on session instance |\n556: | `read_token_from_file` | `patch(\"agentcube.clients.control_plane.read_token_from_file\")` | Avoids filesystem dependency |\n557: | `os.environ` | `patch.dict(os.environ, {...}, clear=True)` | Environment isolation |\n558: | `SA_TOKEN_PATH` | `patch(\"agentcube.clients.control_plane.SA_TOKEN_PATH\", \"/tmp/token\")` | Redirect SA token path |\n559: \n560: ### 5.5 Test Execution\n561: \n562: ```bash\n563: # Run all Python SDK tests\n564: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v\n565: \n566: # Run with coverage\n567: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n568: \n569: # Run specific test file\n570: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py -v\n571: \n572: # Run specific test class\n573: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestStop -v\n574: \n575: # Run only the newly added tests (by keyword)\n576: cd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_stop_when_session\"\n577: ```\n578: \n579: ### 5.6 Coverage Targets\n580: \n581: | Module | Current (est.) | Target |\n582: |--------|---------------|--------|\n583: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | ~75% (3 stop tests not running) | >95% |\n584: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | ~90% | >95% |\n585: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n586: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n587: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n588: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | ~95% | 100% |\n589: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | ~90% | 100% |\n590: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | ~80% | 100% |\n591: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | ~70% | >90% |\n592: | **Overall** | ~82% | >92% |\n593: \n594: ### 5.7 Risk Areas\n595: \n596: | Risk | Mitigation |\n597: |------|-----------|\n598: | `stop()` methods missing `test_` prefix | Fix immediately — 3 tests silently skipped |\n599: | `close()` idempotency on `requests.Session` | `Session.close()` is safe to call multiple times; tests verify call count |\n600: | Environment variable leakage between tests | Use `patch.dict(os.environ, ..., clear=True)` consistently |\n601: | Logger handler duplication across tests | `get_logger` checks `if not logger.handlers`; test verifies this |\n602: | Base64 encoding edge cases (empty, unicode) | Test with `\"\"`, unicode strings, binary-like content |\n603: | Timeout buffer logic (`+2.0`) | Test with various timeout values to verify buffer applied correctly |\n604: | `urljoin` behavior with trailing slashes | Test both with and without trailing slash on router_url |\n605: \n606: ### 5.8 CI Integration\n607: \n608: The existing CI workflow (`.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml`) runs:\n609: ```yaml\n610: python -m pytest tests/ -v\n611: ```\n612: \n613: No changes needed to CI config. New tests will be picked up automatically by pytest discovery.\n614: \n615: Lint workflow (`.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`) uses `ruff` — ensure new test files pass lint:\n616: ```bash\n617: python3 -m ruff check python-sdk/tests/ --config pyproject.toml\n618: ```\n\n(End of file - total 618 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 单元测试 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers comprehensive Python unit tests for the `agentcube-sdk` package (`sdk-python/`). The SDK provides high-level Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n\n### 1.2 Scope\n\n| Module | File | Lines | Test File | Status |\n|--------|------|-------|-----------|--------|\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` | 161 | `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | **Partial** — 635 lines, but 3 methods missing `test_` prefix (won't run) |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` | 79 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** — 837 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` | 96 | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **Good** — 370 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | 176 | `tests/test_data_plane.py` | **Good** — 641 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 80 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes | 21 | `tests/test_exceptions.py` | **Good** — 77 lines |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` | 14 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` | 7 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing edge cases |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775897900100,"end":1775897900113}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897901271,"sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc374d3001oVd01z1KE8AF6X","messageID":"msg_d7bc361990013fLYSD85PJds6n","sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e36eee4184ce4e90868abe82","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775897901251,"end":1775897901268}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897903154,"sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc37a06001CFkXVEgMvGG4Eh","messageID":"msg_d7bc361990013fLYSD85PJds6n","sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7f167dabaab94f59b5423e14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 为 AgentCube 实现 Dify 平台插件集成，使 Dify 用户能够直接在 Agent 工作流中调用 AgentCube 的代码解释器（Code Interpreter）能力。该插件遵循 Dify 插件规范，提供工具提供者（Tool Provider）注册、参数模式声明、凭证校验和工具调用委托，将 Dify 的工具调用请求转发至 AgentCube SDK 的 `CodeInterpreterClient`。\n6: \n7: 同时提供 PCAP Analyzer 示例应用，展示如何在 FastAPI + LangChain/LangGraph 架构中使用 AgentCube 沙箱进行文件分析（上传、脚本生成、执行、重试、报告生成），并配套 Docker 容器化和 Kubernetes 部署配置。\n8: \n9: ## Scope\n10: \n11: ### In Scope\n12: \n13: 1. **Dify 插件核心文件**（`integrations/dify-plugin/`）\n14: \n15:    | 文件 | 说明 |\n16:    |------|------|\n17:    | `main.py` | 插件入口：`Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n18:    | `manifest.yaml` | 根插件清单：元数据、工具提供者注册、资源权限、Runner 声明 |\n19:    | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | 工具提供者描述符：identity、工具列表、Python 入口 |\n20:    | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` — 凭证校验骨架 |\n21:    | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | 工具参数模式（router_url、workload_manager_url、language、code、command、session_id、session_reuse、code_interpreter_id） |\n22:    | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` — `_invoke` 委托给 `execute()`，调用 `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient` |\n23:    | `requirements.txt` | 依赖：`dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` + `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` |\n24:    | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | 文档与打包配置 |\n25: \n26: 2. **工具提供者实现**\n27:    - `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider._validate_credentials()` — 凭证校验框架，失败时抛 `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`\n28:    - OAuth 辅助方法作为注释保留（不激活）\n29: \n30: 3. **工具调用实现**\n31:    - `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool._invoke()` — 接收 `tool_parameters`，调用 `execute()`，yield `create_json_message(result)`\n32:    - `execute()` — 参数：`router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language=\"python\"`, `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse`；委托给 `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient` 执行远程操作\n33: \n34: 4. **PCAP Analyzer 示例应用**（`example/pcap-analyzer/`）\n35: \n36:    | 文件 | 说明 |\n37:    |------|------|\n38:    | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI 应用：LangChain/LangGraph Agent 组合、`SandboxRunner` 封装、分析编排（计划→执行→重试→报告） |\n39:    | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI、uvicorn、LangChain/LangGraph 完整依赖链 |\n40:    | `Dockerfile` | `uv` 基础镜像，安装依赖，vendor `agentcube` SDK，暴露 8000 |\n41:    | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment：资源配置、环境变量、Secret 挂载 |\n42:    | `README.md` | 文档 |\n43: \n44: 5. **PCAP Analyzer 核心组件**\n45:    - `SandboxRunner` — 封装沙箱交互：`upload_file`, `upload_bytes`, `run`, `stop`\n46:    - Agent 构建：`build_react_agent`, `build_planner_agent`, `build_reporter_agent`\n47:    - 分析编排：`_plan_script`, `_repair_script`, `_execute_once_in_runner`, `_analyze_with_retries`, `_report`\n48:    - `POST /analyze` 端点：接受 PCAP 文件上传或路径，返回 `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n49: \n50: 6. **配置管理**\n51:    - 环境变量：`OPENAI_API_KEY`（必填）, `OPENAI_API_BASE`（默认 `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`）, `OPENAI_MODEL`（默认 `Qwen/QwQ-32B`）, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`\n52:    - 启动时校验 API Key，缺失则拒绝启动\n53: \n54: ### Out of Scope\n55: \n56: - Dify 插件市场发布和审核流程\n57: - OAuth 凭证流程的完整实现（仅保留注释骨架）\n58: - 多工具提供者扩展（当前仅 `agentcube-code-interpreter`）\n59: - PCAP Analyzer 的 Service/Ingress Kubernetes 资源\n60: - 异步 I/O 版本的 SDK 调用\n61: - 流式输出（SSE）支持\n62: - 其他文件格式分析（仅 PCAP 示例）\n63: \n64: ## Impact Analysis\n65: \n66: ### Dependencies\n67: \n68: | 依赖 | 来源 | 说明 |\n69: |------|------|------|\n70: | `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` | PyPI | Dify 插件框架 |\n71: | `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` | 本地/PyPI | AgentCube Python SDK（`CodeInterpreterClient`） |\n72: | `fastapi`, `uvicorn` | PyPI | PCAP Analyzer Web 框架 |\n73: | `langchain-*`, `langgraph-*` | PyPI | PCAP Analyzer Agent 框架 |\n74: | `paramiko` | PyPI | PCAP Analyzer SSH/SFTP 支持 |\n75: \n76: ### Affected Components\n77: \n78: | 文件/目录 | 状态 | 说明 |\n79: |-----------|------|------|\n80: | `integrations/dify-plugin/` | 新增 | Dify 插件完整目录结构 |\n81: | `integrations/design.md` | 已存在 | 设计参考文档 |\n82: | `integrations/spec.md` | 已存在 | 规范文档 |\n83: | `example/pcap-analyzer/` | 新增 | PCAP 分析示例应用 |\n84: | `python-sdk/` | 无变更 | 作为依赖被引用（`agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`） |\n85: \n86: ### 与现有组件的交互\n87: \n88: | 组件 | 交互方式 | 影响 |\n89: |------|----------|------|\n90: | `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient` | Dify 工具调用委托 | 复用 SDK 的 session 管理、文件上传、代码执行能力 |\n91: | Dify 平台 | 插件注册和工具调用 | 遵循 Dify 插件生命周期和消息协议 |\n92: | Router / Workload Manager | 控制面 + 数据面 HTTP | SDK 内部处理，插件只需传递 URL 参数 |\n93: | LangChain/LangGraph | PCAP Analyzer Agent 编排 | 通过 `SandboxRunner` 间接使用 SDK |\n94: \n95: ### Risk Assessment\n96: \n97: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n98: |------|------|----------|\n99: | `dify-plugin` 版本不兼容 | 高 | 严格 pin `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`，测试覆盖边界版本 |\n100: | `agentcube-sdk` 版本不匹配 | 高 | pin `>=0.0.10`，与 SDK 发布同步验证 |\n101: | 凭证校验逻辑缺失导致不安全连接 | 中 | `_validate_credentials` 提供骨架，实施者需填充校验逻辑 |\n102: | PCAP 文件过大导致内存溢出 | 中 | `SandboxRunner` 使用流式上传（`upload_bytes`），限制文件大小 |\n103: | Agent 脚本生成失败导致无限重试 | 中 | `_analyze_with_retries` 限制 `max_retries=2` |\n104: | K8s Secret 未正确配置导致启动失败 | 低 | `deployment.yaml` 明确声明 Secret 引用，启动时校验 |\n105: \n106: ## Alternatives Considered\n107: \n108: ### 1. Dify 插件 vs. 自定义 API Gateway（✅ 选定 Dify 插件）\n109: \n110: **做法**：实现 Dify 官方插件规范，而非自建 API Gateway 适配层。\n111: \n112: **优点**：\n113: - 原生集成 Dify 工具生态，用户无需额外配置\n114: - 遵循 Dify 插件生命周期，平台自动管理加载/卸载\n115: - 多语言标签支持（`zh_Hans`, `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `pt_BR`）开箱即用\n116: - 资源权限声明（memory、permission）由 Dify 沙箱强制执行\n117: \n118: **缺点**：\n119: - 绑定 Dify 插件框架 API，版本升级需适配\n120: - `dify-plugin` 库引入额外依赖\n121: \n122: **决策**：采用 Dify 插件方案。目标用户群体使用 Dify 平台，原生集成体验最佳。\n123: \n124: ### 2. 单工具 vs. 多工具提供者（✅ 选定单工具）\n125: \n126: **做法**：当前仅提供 `agentcube-code-interpreter` 单一工具，而非拆分为多个工具（如 `upload-file`, `run-code`, `execute-command`）。\n127: \n128: **优点**：\n129: - 简化用户配置（一次选择工具，填写所有参数）\n130: - 减少 Dify 工作流中的节点数量\n131: - 与 `CodeInterpreterClient` 的门面模式一致\n132: \n133: **缺点**：\n134: - 参数较多（8 个），用户理解成本高\n135: - 无法在 Dify 中单独禁用某个子操作\n136: \n137: **决策**：采用单工具方案。当前场景下代码解释器是原子操作，拆分收益不大。未来如需细粒度控制可通过独立 AR 添加。\n138: \n139: ### 3. 同步执行 vs. 异步任务队列（✅ 选定同步）\n140: \n141: **做法**：工具调用同步等待执行结果返回，而非提交异步任务后轮询。\n142: \n143: **优点**：\n144: - 实现简单，符合 Dify 工具调用模型（`_invoke` 返回 `Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]`）\n145: - `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120` 足够覆盖大多数代码执行场景\n146: - 无需额外的任务状态存储和轮询逻辑\n147: \n148: **缺点**：\n149: - 长时间运行的任务可能超时\n150: - 阻塞 Dify 工作流直到执行完成\n151: \n152: **决策**：采用同步方案。120 秒超时对代码解释器场景合理。如需长任务支持，可通过 `session_reuse` + 分段执行实现。\n153: \n154: ### 4. PCAP Analyzer：LangGraph vs. 纯代码编排（✅ 选定 LangGraph）\n155: \n156: **做法**：使用 LangGraph 的 ReAct Agent 模式进行脚本生成和修复，而非纯 Python 代码编排。\n157: \n158: **优点**：\n159: - LLM 自主决策脚本生成和修复策略\n160: - ReAct 模式天然支持工具调用和反思\n161: - `create_react_agent` 开箱即用，减少样板代码\n162: \n163: **缺点**：\n164: - 引入 LangChain/LangGraph 依赖链（约 10+ 包）\n165: - LLM 输出不确定性可能导致脚本质量波动\n166: - 调试复杂度增加\n167: \n168: **决策**：采用 LangGraph 方案。PCAP 分析是探索性任务，LLM 自主规划比硬编码脚本更灵活。通过 `_analyze_with_retries`（最多 2 次重试）缓解输出质量问题。\n169: \n170: ### 5. uv vs. pip/conda 依赖管理（✅ 选定 uv）\n171: \n172: **做法**：使用 `uv` 作为 Python 包管理器和运行时，而非传统 `pip` + `venv`。\n173: \n174: **优点**：\n175: - 安装速度显著快于 pip（Rust 实现）\n176: - `uv run` 自动管理虚拟环境，简化容器入口\n177: - 与 `pyproject.toml` / `requirements.txt` 兼容\n178: \n179: **缺点**：\n180: - 相对较新的工具，生态成熟度不如 pip\n181: - 团队成员可能需要学习新工具\n182: \n183: **决策**：采用 uv。容器化场景下安装速度优势明显，且 Dockerfile 中只需单条 `uv pip install` 命令。\n184: \n185: ## Implementation Notes\n186: \n187: ### Dify 插件目录结构\n188: \n189: ```\n190: integrations/dify-plugin/\n191: ├── main.py                          # Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()\n192: ├── manifest.yaml                    # 根清单\n193: ├── requirements.txt                 # dify-plugin + agentcube-sdk\n194: ├── GUIDE.md\n195: ├── README.md\n196: ├── PRIVACY.md\n197: ├── .difyignore\n198: ├── provider/\n199: │   ├── agentcube.yaml               # 工具提供者描述符\n200: │   └── agentcube.py                 # AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider\n201: └── tools/\n202:     ├── agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml  # 工具参数模式\n203:     └── agentcube-code-interpreter.py    # AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool\n204: ```\n205: \n206: ### manifest.yaml 关键字段\n207: \n208: ```yaml\n209: version: \"0.0.2\"\n210: type: plugin\n211: author: volcano-sh\n212: name: agentcube\n213: label:\n214:   en_US: Agentcube\n215:   ja_JP: Agentcube\n216:   zh_Hans: Agentcube\n217:   pt_BR: Agentcube\n218: description:\n219:   en_US: AgentCube description\n220:   # ... 其他语言\n221: icon: icon.png\n222: icon_dark: icon-dark.png\n223: resource:\n224:   memory: ...\n225:   permission:\n226:     tool: ...\n227:     model: ...\n228:     endpoint: ...\n229:     app: ...\n230:     storage: ...\n231: plugins:\n232:   tools:\n233:     - provider/agentcube.yaml\n234: meta:\n235:   version: ...\n236:   arch:\n237:     - amd64\n238:     - arm64\n239:   runner:\n240:     language: python\n241:     version: \"3.12\"\n242:     entrypoint: main\n243:   minimum_dify_version: null\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### 工具参数模式\n247: \n248: | 参数 | 类型 | 必填 | 说明 |\n249: |------|------|------|------|\n250: | `router_url` | string | 是 | Router 端点 URL |\n251: | `workload_manager_url` | string | 是 | Workload Manager 端点 URL |\n252: | `language` | select | 否 | `python`, `javascript`, `typescript`（默认 `python`） |\n253: | `code` | string | 否 | 要执行的代码 |\n254: | `command` | string | 否 | 要执行的 shell 命令 |\n255: | `session_id` | string | 否 | 复用已有 session |\n256: | `session_reuse` | boolean | 否 | 是否复用 session |\n257: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | 否 | 指定解释器实例 |\n258: \n259: ### AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool.execute() 实现要点\n260: \n261: ```python\n262: def execute(\n263:     self,\n264:     router_url=None,\n265:     workload_manager_url=None,\n266:     language=\"python\",\n267:     code_interpreter_id=None,\n268:     session_id=None,\n269:     code=None,\n270:     command=None,\n271:     session_reuse=False,\n272:     **kwargs\n273: ):\n274:     # 1. 构造 CodeInterpreterClient(router_url=router_url, workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url, ...)\n275:     # 2. 根据 code/command 参数选择执行路径：\n276:     #    - code 非空 → client.run_code(language, code)\n277:     #    - command 非空 → client.execute_command(command)\n278:     # 3. 返回 JSON 可序列化结果\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ### PCAP Analyzer 架构\n282: \n283: ```\n284: ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n285: │  FastAPI    │────▶│  Planner     │────▶│  SandboxRunner  │\n286: │  /analyze   │     │  Agent       │     │  (AgentCube)    │\n287: └─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n288:                            │                     │\n289:                            ▼                     ▼\n290:                     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n291:                     │  Repair      │◀────│  Script         │\n292:                     │  Agent       │     │  Execution      │\n293:                     └──────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n294:                            │\n295:                            ▼\n296:                     ┌──────────────┐\n297:                     │  Reporter    │\n298:                     │  Agent       │\n299:                     └──────────────┘\n300: ```\n301: \n302: **请求流程**：\n303: 1. `POST /analyze` 接收 PCAP 文件 → 上传到沙箱\n304: 2. Planner Agent 生成分析脚本\n305: 3. `_execute_once_in_runner` 在沙箱中执行\n306: 4. 失败时 Repair Agent 修正脚本，最多重试 2 次\n307: 5. Reporter Agent 聚合结果生成报告\n308: 6. 返回 `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n309: \n310: ### K8s Deployment 关键配置\n311: \n312: ```yaml\n313: resources:\n314:   requests:\n315:     cpu: 200m\n316:     memory: 100Mi\n317:   limits:\n318:     cpu: \"1\"\n319:     memory: 1Gi\n320: env:\n321:   - name: OPENAI_API_KEY\n322:     valueFrom:\n323:       secretKeyRef:\n324:         name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n325:         key: openai-api-key\n326:   - name: OPENAI_API_BASE\n327:     value: ...\n328:   # ... 其他环境变量\n329: command: [\"uv\"]\n330: args: [\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### 测试策略\n334: \n335: - **Dify 插件单元测试**：mock `dify_plugin.Tool` 和 `CodeInterpreterClient`，验证 `_invoke` 委托和 `execute` 参数传递\n336: - **凭证校验测试**：模拟有效/无效凭证，验证 `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` 抛出\n337: - **PCAP Analyzer 集成测试**：mock LLM 响应和 SandboxRunner，验证分析流程编排\n338: - **Manifest 校验**：验证 YAML 结构符合 Dify 插件规范要求\n339: \n340: ## Acceptance Criteria\n341: \n342: 1. **Dify 插件**\n343:    - [ ] `main.py` 入口正确执行 `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n344:    - [ ] `manifest.yaml` 包含所有必需字段（version, type, author, name, label, description, icon, resource, plugins.tools, meta）\n345:    - [ ] `provider/agentcube.yaml` 正确声明 identity、tools 列表、extra.python.source\n346:    - [ ] `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` 参数模式与 spec 一致（8 个参数，类型/必填/选项正确）\n347:    - [ ] `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider._validate_credentials()` 在错误时抛 `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`\n348:    - [ ] `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool._invoke()` 正确委托给 `execute()` 并 yield JSON message\n349:    - [ ] `execute()` 调用 `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient` 执行远程操作\n350:    - [ ] `requirements.txt` 满足 `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` 和 `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n351: \n352: 2. **PCAP Analyzer**\n353:    - [ ] 启动时校验 `OPENAI_API_KEY`，缺失则拒绝启动\n354:    - [ ] `POST /analyze` 接受文件上传或路径，返回 `AnalyzeResponse`\n355:    - [ ] `SandboxRunner` 支持 `upload_file`, `upload_bytes`, `run`, `stop`\n356:    - [ ] 分析流程支持最多 2 次脚本修复重试\n357:    - [ ] 默认配置：`OPENAI_API_BASE=https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL=Qwen/QwQ-32B`\n358: \n359: 3. **容器化与部署**\n360:    - [ ] Dockerfile 使用 `uv` 基础镜像，正确 vendor `agentcube` SDK\n361:    - [ ] K8s Deployment 资源配置、Secret 挂载、环境变量与 spec 一致\n362:    - [ ] 容器默认命令为 `uv run pcap_analyzer.py`，暴露端口 8000\n363: \n364: 4. **代码质量**\n365:    - [ ] 完整类型注解\n366:    - [ ] 所有公开方法有 docstring\n367:    - [ ] 通过 lint/typecheck\n368: \n369: ## Status\n370: \n371: - [ ] 提案审查\n372: - [ ] 实现\n373: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 373 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube 实现 Dify 平台插件集成，使 Dify 用户能够直接在 Agent 工作流中调用 AgentCube 的代码解释器（Code Interpreter）能力。该插件遵循 Dify 插件规范，提供工具提供者（Tool Provider）注册、参数模式声明、凭证校验和工具调用委托，将 Dify 的工具调用请求转发至 AgentCube SDK 的 `CodeInterpreterClient`。\n\n同时提供 PCAP Analyzer 示例应用，展示如何在 FastAPI + LangChain/LangGraph 架构中使用 AgentCube 沙箱进行文件分析（上传、脚本生成、执行、重试、报告生成），并配套 Docker 容器化和 Kubernetes 部署配置。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Dify 插件核心文件**（`integrations/dify-plugin/`）\n\n   | 文件 | 说明 |\n   |------|------|\n   | `main.py` | 插件入口：`Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n   | `manifest.yaml` | 根插件清单：元数据、工具提供者注册、资源权限、Runner 声明 |\n   | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | 工具提供者描述符：identity、工具列表、Python 入口 |\n   | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` — 凭证校验骨架 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775897903141,"end":1775897903151}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775897905415,"sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc380b7001xpP0Qee54Af2hE","messageID":"msg_d7bc361990013fLYSD85PJds6n","sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_0ef58af417254063a7ec8111","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n4: **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n9: \n10: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n11: - [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n12: - [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n13: - [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\n14: \n15: ## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\n16: \n17: - [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\n18: - [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n19: - [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n20: - [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple\n21: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_id` raises `ValueError`\n22: - [ ] Write test: missing `agent_endpoint` raises `ValueError`\n23: \n24: ## T-3: InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation\n25: \n26: - [ ] Implement `_direct_http_invocation(endpoint: str, payload: Dict, headers: Dict[str, str], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict`\n27: - [ ] POST JSON to `{endpoint}` using `httpx` (sync client)\n28: - [ ] Parse JSON response; return parsed dict\n29: - [ ] On non-2xx status, raise exception with status code and response body\n30: - [ ] Write test: successful POST returns parsed JSON response\n31: - [ ] Write test: non-2xx response raises exception with status code\n32: - [ ] Write test: custom headers are included in request\n33: \n34: ## T-4: InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube\n35: \n36: - [ ] Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path) -> Dict`\n37: - [ ] Load metadata; if `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrite endpoint to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n38: - [ ] If `metadata.session_id` exists, inject header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id`\n39: - [ ] POST JSON to rewritten endpoint; return parsed response\n40: - [ ] Write test: endpoint rewriting when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n41: - [ ] Write test: session header injection when `session_id` present\n42: - [ ] Write test: no rewriting when deployment type is not `AgentRuntime`\n43: - [ ] Write test: no session header when `session_id` is absent\n44: \n45: ## T-5: InvokeRuntime.invoke (orchestration)\n46: \n47: - [ ] Implement `invoke(workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict, headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict`\n48: - [ ] Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` → get metadata, agent_id, endpoint\n49: - [ ] If `self.provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n50: - [ ] Otherwise, call `_direct_http_invocation`\n51: - [ ] Return the response\n52: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n53: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_direct_http_invocation`\n54: \n55: ## T-6: invoke CLI command entry point\n56: \n57: - [ ] Add `invoke()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n58: - [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `payload` (`--payload`, default `\"{}\"`), `header_list` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n59: - [ ] Parse `--payload` as JSON; on invalid JSON, print `Error: Invalid JSON payload: {detail}` in red, exit code `1`\n60: - [ ] Parse `--header` entries: split on first `:`, strip key/value; on missing `:`, print `Error: Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'.` in red, exit code `1`\n61: - [ ] Merge multiple headers into single `Dict[str, str]`\n62: - [ ] Call `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` within error handler\n63: - [ ] On success, print response (Rich-formatted if JSON, raw text otherwise)\n64: - [ ] On error, use `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)`\n65: - [ ] Write test: successful invoke prints response, exit 0\n66: - [ ] Write test: invalid JSON payload → error message, exit 1\n67: - [ ] Write test: invalid header format → error message, exit 1\n68: - [ ] Write test: multiple headers merged correctly\n69: - [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n70: - [ ] Write test: quiet error prints message only, exit 1\n71: \n72: ## T-7: StatusRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n73: \n74: - [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with `StatusRuntime` class\n75: - [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n76: - [ ] Add `StatusRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n77: - [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly\n78: \n79: ## T-8: StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status\n80: \n81: - [ ] Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n82: - [ ] Use `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(name)` to fetch CR\n83: - [ ] If CR exists and has `status` field → return `{\"status\": cr_status, \"endpoint\": cr_agentEndpoint, ...}`\n84: - [ ] If CR exists but no `status` field → return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}`\n85: - [ ] If CR not found → return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}`\n86: - [ ] Write test: CR exists with status → returns status + endpoint\n87: - [ ] Write test: CR exists without status → returns `created_no_status`\n88: - [ ] Write test: CR not found → returns `not_found_in_k8s`\n89: \n90: ## T-9: StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status\n91: \n92: - [ ] Implement `_get_k8s_status(metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict`\n93: - [ ] Call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)` (see T-11)\n94: - [ ] Return the result dict\n95: - [ ] Write test: calls `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and returns result\n96: \n97: ## T-10: StatusRuntime.get_status (orchestration)\n98: \n99: - [ ] Implement `get_status(workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict`\n100: - [ ] Load metadata from workspace via `MetadataService`\n101: - [ ] If no `agent_id` → return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n102: - [ ] If `provider == \"agentcube\"` (or default), call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n103: - [ ] Otherwise, call `_get_k8s_status`\n104: - [ ] Return the status dict\n105: - [ ] Write test: no `agent_id` → returns `not_published`\n106: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"agentcube\" routes to `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n107: - [ ] Write test: provider=\"k8s\" routes to `_get_k8s_status`\n108: \n109: ## T-11: KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status\n110: \n111: - [ ] Add `get_agent_status(agent_name: str) -> Dict` to `KubernetesProvider`\n112: - [ ] Query deployment status via `AppsV1Api.read_namespaced_deployment_status`\n113: - [ ] Query pod status via `CoreV1Api.list_namespaced_pod` with label selector\n114: - [ ] Return dict with deployment status, pod statuses, endpoint info\n115: - [ ] On 404, return `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}`\n116: - [ ] Write test: deployment found with ready pods → returns status\n117: - [ ] Write test: deployment not found → returns `not_found`\n118: \n119: ## T-12: status CLI command entry point\n120: \n121: - [ ] Add `status()` command to `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n122: - [ ] Options: `workspace` (`-f`, default `\".\"`), `provider` (`--provider`, default `\"agentcube\"`), `verbose` (`--verbose`, default `False`)\n123: - [ ] Call `StatusRuntime.get_status()`\n124: - [ ] If status == `\"not_published\"` → print guidance to run `publish` first, exit code `1`\n125: - [ ] If status == `\"error\"` → print error details, exit code `1`\n126: - [ ] Otherwise, render Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value (at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider)\n127: - [ ] On exception, use `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)`\n128: - [ ] Write test: not_published → guidance message, exit 1\n129: - [ ] Write test: error status → error details, exit 1\n130: - [ ] Write test: valid status → Rich Table rendered with required fields\n131: - [ ] Write test: verbose error prints traceback, exit 1\n132: \n133: ## T-13: Provider validation (cross-cutting)\n134: \n135: - [ ] Add provider validation to both `invoke` and `status` commands: reject values other than `\"agentcube\"` / `\"k8s\"`\n136: - [ ] Write test: invalid provider → error message, exit 1\n137: \n138: ## T-14: Integration tests\n139: \n140: - [ ] Write integration test: full invoke flow with mocked HTTP (mock `httpx.Client`)\n141: - [ ] Write integration test: full status flow with mocked K8s (mock `AgentCubeProvider` / `KubernetesProvider`)\n142: - [ ] Write integration test: invoke with session header end-to-end (mocked)\n143: \n144: ## T-15: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n145: \n146: - [ ] `ruff check agentcube/` — no violations\n147: - [ ] `mypy agentcube/` — no type errors\n148: - [ ] `pytest tests/ -v` — all pass\n149: - [ ] `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — coverage ≥ 80%\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## Dependency Graph\n154: \n155: ```\n156: T-1  ──┬── T-2 ──┬── T-5 ── T-6\n157:        │          │\n158:        │          └── T-4 ──┘\n159:        │\n160:        └── T-3 ──┘\n161: \n162: T-7  ──┬── T-8 ──┬── T-10 ── T-12\n163:        │          │\n164:        └── T-9 ──┘  (T-9 depends on T-11)\n165: \n166: T-11 ── T-9\n167: \n168: T-13 ── (T-6, T-12)\n169: \n170: T-14 ── (T-6, T-12)\n171: \n172: T-15 ── (all above)\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ## Parallelizable Groups\n176: \n177: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n178: |-------|-------|---------------|\n179: | G1 | T-1, T-7 | None |\n180: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-11 | T-1 |\n181: | G3 | T-4, T-8, T-9 | T-2, T-11 |\n182: | G4 | T-5, T-10 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-8, T-9 |\n183: | G5 | T-6, T-12, T-13 | T-5, T-10 |\n184: | G6 | T-14 | T-6, T-12 |\n185: | G7 | T-15 | All above |\n\n(End of file - total 185 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `delta-spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## T-1: InvokeRuntime class skeleton + constructor\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n- [ ] Implement `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\")` setting `self.verbose` and `self.provider`\n- [ ] Add `InvokeRuntime` export to `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor sets `verbose` and `provider` correctly (default and explicit values)\n\n## T-2: InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites\n\n- [ ] Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path: Path) -> tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]`\n- [ ] Load metadata via `MetadataService`; raise `ValueError` if `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint` is missing\n- [ ] Return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n- [ ] Write test: valid workspace with published metadata returns tuple","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775897905407,"end":1775897905413}}}}
