{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775897927847,"sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc3e0a4001JzePmX1V7Gxql8","messageID":"msg_d7bc3da5f001ovSLeqZObAuOdn","sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775898088185,"sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","part":{"id":"prt_d7bc3f166001HWEEgUrrutLdWt","messageID":"msg_d7bc3da5f001ovSLeqZObAuOdn","sessionID":"ses_2843cba31ffeB5jipUyIoDGq0I","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_1633dc9c22c34eebb36b5a10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-042: Docusaurus 文档站框架 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR establishes a Docusaurus 3.x documentation site for AgentCube, providing versioned documentation, multi-language support (en/zh), search, and automated CI/CD deployment. The docs site serves as the primary developer and user-facing documentation for the Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform.\n\n### 1.2 Scope\n\n| Component | Description | Status |\n|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| Docusaurus 3.x project scaffold | `docs/` directory with full site configuration | **New** |\n| Documentation content structure | Organized docs by audience and topic | **New** |\n| Versioned documentation | Docusaurus versioning for release docs | **New** |\n| Multi-language (i18n) | English + Simplified Chinese | **New** |\n| Search integration | Algolia DocSearch or local search | **New** |\n| CI/CD deployment | GitHub Pages or custom domain via GitHub Actions | **New** |\n| Custom theme configuration | AgentCube branding, colors, logo | **New** |\n| MDX support | Interactive docs with React components | **New** |\n\n### 1.3 System Context\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Docusaurus 3.x Site                        │\n│                                                                │\n│  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Markdown  │  │    MDX     │  │   React Components     │  │\n│  │  /docs/    │  │  (inline)  │  │   /src/components/     │  │\n│  └─────┬──────┘  └─────┬──────┘  └──────────┬─────────────┘  │\n│        │               │                     │                 │\n│  ┌─────▼───────────────▼─────────────────────▼─────────────┐  │\n│  │              Docusaurus Build Pipeline                    │  │\n│  │         (webpack/babel → static HTML/JS/CSS)             │  │\n│  └────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                           │                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────▼────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │              Static Output (build/)                       │  │\n│  └────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└───────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n              ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n              │   GitHub Pages / CDN        │\n              │   (docs.agentcube.dev)      │\n              └─────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n              ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n              │   End Users / Developers    │\n              └─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.4 Design Principles\n\n- **Docs-as-code**: Documentation lives in the same repository, reviewed via PRs, versioned with releases.\n- **Progressive disclosure**: Quick start for new users, deep dives for advanced operators.\n- **Version-aligned**: Documentation versions track AgentCube release tags (v0.x, v1.x, etc.).\n- **Bilingual by default**: All content authored in English with Chinese translations; fallback to English for untranslated pages.\n- **Searchable**: Full-text search across all versions and languages.\n\n### 1.5 Directory Structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── package.json                          # Node.js dependencies\n├── docusaurus.config.ts                  # Site configuration (TypeScript)\n├── sidebars.ts                           # Sidebar navigation definitions\n├── babel.config.js                       # Babel config (if needed)\n├── tsconfig.json                         # TypeScript configuration\n├── src/\n│   ├── css/\n│   │   └── custom.css                   # Global CSS overrides\n│   ├── components/\n│   │   ├── HomepageFeatures/\n│   │   │   ├── index.tsx\n│   │   │   └── styles.module.css\n│   │   ├── ApiEndpoint/                  # MDX component for API docs\n│   │   │   └── index.tsx\n│   │   └── K8sResource/                  # MDX component for CRD docs\n│   │       └── index.tsx\n│   ├── pages/\n│   │   ├── index.tsx                    # Landing page\n│   │   ├── index.module.css\n│   │   └── markdown-page.md\n│   └── theme/                            # Swizzled theme components\n│       ├── Footer/\n│       │   └── index.tsx\n│       └── Navbar/\n│           └── Logo/\n│               └── index.tsx\n├── docs/\n│   ├── intro.md                          # Introduction / Overview\n│   ├── getting-started/\n│   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   ├── installation.md\n│   │   ├── quick-start.md\n│   │   └── configuration.md\n│   ├── architecture/\n│   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   ├── overview.md\n│   │   ├── components.md\n│   │   ├── session-routing.md\n│   │   └── sandbox-lifecycle.md\n│   ├── user-guide/\n│   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   ├── code-interpreter.md\n│   │   ├── agent-runtime.md\n│   │   ├── cli.md\n│   │   └── python-sdk.md\n│   ├── api-reference/\n│   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   ├── control-plane.md\n│   │   ├── data-plane.md\n│   │   └── crds.md\n│   ├── integrations/\n│   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   ├── dify-plugin.md\n│   │   └── langchain.md\n│   ├── operations/\n│   │   ├── _category_.json\n│   │   ├── deployment.md\n│   │   ├── monitoring.md\n│   │   ├── troubleshooting.md\n│   │   └── security.md\n│   └── contributing/\n│       ├── _category_.json\n│       ├── development.md\n│       ├── testing.md\n│       └── release-process.md\n├── versioned_docs/\n│   └── version-0.1.x/                    # Auto-generated by docusaurus docs:version\n│       └── ...                           # Snapshot of docs at release time\n├── versioned_sidebars/\n│   └── version-0.1.x-sidebars.json       # Sidebar snapshot per version\n├── versions.json                         # List of available versions\n└── i18n/\n    └── zh/\n        ├── docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/\n        │   ├── current/                  # Translated docs (mirrors docs/)\n        │   │   ├── intro.md\n        │   │   ├── getting-started/\n        │   │   ├── architecture/\n        │   │   └── ...\n        │   └── current.json              # Category/label translations\n        ├── docusaurus-theme-classic/\n        │   ├── navbar.json               # Navbar label translations\n        │   └── footer.json               # Footer label translations\n        └── code.json                     # UI string translations\n```\n\n### 1.6 Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `@docusaurus/core` | ^3.7.0 | Core framework |\n| `@docusaurus/preset-classic` | ^3.7.0 | Classic theme (docs, blog, pages) |\n| `@docusaurus/module-type-aliases` | ^3.7.0 | TypeScript type aliases |\n| `@docusaurus/tsconfig` | ^3.7.0 | TypeScript base config |\n| `@docusaurus/types` | ^3.7.0 | TypeScript types |\n| `@mdx-js/react` | ^3.0.0 | MDX rendering |\n| `clsx` | ^2.0.0 | Conditional CSS class utility |\n| `prism-react-renderer` | ^2.3.0 | Code block syntax highlighting |\n| `react` | ^19.0.0 | UI framework |\n| `react-dom` | ^19.0.0 | DOM rendering |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-client-redirects` | ^3.7.0 | Redirect rules (optional) |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-ideal-image` | ^3.7.0 | Responsive images (optional) |\n| `@easyops-cn/docusaurus-search-local` | ^0.48.0 | Local search (fallback for DocSearch) |\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Site Configuration (`docusaurus.config.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nimport { themes as prismThemes } from 'prism-react-renderer';\nimport type { Config } from '@docusaurus/types';\nimport type * as Preset from '@docusaurus/preset-classic';\n\nconst config: Config = {\n  title: 'AgentCube',\n  tagline: 'Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agents',\n  favicon: 'img/favicon.ico',\n  url: 'https://docs.agentcube.dev',\n  baseUrl: '/',\n  organizationName: 'volcano-sh',\n  projectName: 'agentcube',\n  deploymentBranch: 'gh-pages',\n\n  i18n: {\n    defaultLocale: 'en',\n    locales: ['en', 'zh'],\n    localeConfigs: {\n      en: { label: 'English', direction: 'ltr' },\n      zh: { label: '简体中文', direction: 'ltr' },\n    },\n  },\n\n  presets: [\n    [\n      'classic',\n      {\n        docs: {\n          sidebarPath: './sidebars.ts',\n          editUrl: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/tree/main/docs/',\n          showLastUpdateAuthor: true,\n          showLastUpdateTime: true,\n          lastVersion: 'current',\n          versions: {\n            current: {\n              label: 'Next 🚧',\n              path: 'next',\n              badge: true,\n            },\n          },\n        },\n        blog: {\n          showReadingTime: true,\n          editUrl: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/tree/main/docs/',\n        },\n        theme: {\n          customCss: './src/css/custom.css',\n        },\n      } satisfies Preset.Options,\n    ],\n  ],\n\n  themeConfig: {\n    image: 'img/agentcube-social-card.png',\n    navbar: {\n      title: 'AgentCube',\n      logo: { alt: 'AgentCube Logo', src: 'img/logo.svg' },\n      items: [\n        { type: 'docSidebar', sidebarId: 'tutorialSidebar', position: 'left', label: 'Docs' },\n        { to: '/blog', label: 'Blog', position: 'left' },\n        { type: 'docsVersionDropdown', position: 'right' },\n        { type: 'localeDropdown', position: 'right' },\n        {\n          href: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube',\n          label: 'GitHub',\n          position: 'right',\n        },\n      ],\n    },\n    footer: {\n      style: 'dark',\n      links: [\n        {\n          title: 'Docs',\n          items: [\n            { label: 'Getting Started', to: '/docs/getting-started/quick-start' },\n            { label: 'Architecture', to: '/docs/architecture/overview' },\n            { label: 'API Reference', to: '/docs/api-reference/control-plane' },\n          ],\n        },\n        {\n          title: 'Community',\n          items: [\n            { label: 'GitHub Discussions', href: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/discussions' },\n            { label: 'Slack', href: 'https://kubernetes.slack.com/' },\n          ],\n        },\n        {\n          title: 'More',\n          items: [\n            { label: 'Blog', to: '/blog' },\n            { label: 'GitHub', href: 'https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube' },\n          ],\n        },\n      ],\n      copyright: `Copyright © ${new Date().getFullYear()} The AgentCube Authors. Built with Docusaurus.`,\n    },\n    prism: {\n      theme: prismThemes.github,\n      darkTheme: prismThemes.dracula,\n      additionalLanguages: ['bash', 'go', 'python', 'yaml', 'json', 'docker', 'kubernetes'],\n    },\n    algolia: {\n      appId: 'TBD',\n      apiKey: 'TBD',\n      indexName: 'agentcube',\n      contextualSearch: true,\n    },\n  } satisfies Preset.ThemeConfig,\n\n  markdown: {\n    mermaid: true,\n  },\n  themes: ['@docusaurus/theme-mermaid'],\n};\n\nexport default config;\n```\n\n### 2.2 Sidebar Definition (`sidebars.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nimport type { SidebarsConfig } from '@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs';\n\nconst sidebars: SidebarsConfig = {\n  tutorialSidebar: [\n    'intro',\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Getting Started',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'getting-started/installation' },\n      items: [\n        'getting-started/installation',\n        'getting-started/quick-start',\n        'getting-started/configuration',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Architecture',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'architecture/overview' },\n      items: [\n        'architecture/overview',\n        'architecture/components',\n        'architecture/session-routing',\n        'architecture/sandbox-lifecycle',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'User Guide',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'user-guide/code-interpreter' },\n      items: [\n        'user-guide/code-interpreter',\n        'user-guide/agent-runtime',\n        'user-guide/cli',\n        'user-guide/python-sdk',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'API Reference',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'api-reference/control-plane' },\n      items: [\n        'api-reference/control-plane',\n        'api-reference/data-plane',\n        'api-reference/crds',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Integrations',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'integrations/dify-plugin' },\n      items: [\n        'integrations/dify-plugin',\n        'integrations/langchain',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Operations',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'operations/deployment' },\n      items: [\n        'operations/deployment',\n        'operations/monitoring',\n        'operations/troubleshooting',\n        'operations/security',\n      ],\n    },\n    {\n      type: 'category',\n      label: 'Contributing',\n      link: { type: 'doc', id: 'contributing/development' },\n      items: [\n        'contributing/development',\n        'contributing/testing',\n        'contributing/release-process',\n      ],\n    },\n  ],\n};\n\nexport default sidebars;\n```\n\n### 2.3 Category Metadata (`_category_.json`)\n\nEach documentation category directory contains a `_category_.json` file:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Getting Started\",\n  \"position\": 2,\n  \"link\": {\n    \"type\": \"generated-index\",\n    \"description\": \"Learn how to install and get started with AgentCube.\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 2.4 Frontmatter Schema\n\nAll `.md` and `.mdx` files use YAML frontmatter:\n\n```yaml\n---\nsidebar_position: 1\ntitle: Quick Start\ndescription: Get AgentCube running in 5 minutes\nkeywords: [quickstart, installation, kubernetes]\n---\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `sidebar_position` | number | No | Order in sidebar (lower = first) |\n| `title` | string | No | Page title (defaults to filename) |\n| `description` | string | No | Meta description for SEO |\n| `keywords` | string[] | No | SEO keywords |\n| `slug` | string | No | Custom URL path override |\n| `hide_title` | boolean | No | Hide auto-generated title |\n| `sidebar_label` | string | No | Short label for sidebar |\n\n### 2.5 MDX Component Interfaces\n\n#### `ApiEndpoint` — API endpoint documentation block\n\n```tsx\ninterface ApiEndpointProps {\n  method: 'GET' | 'POST' | 'PUT' | 'DELETE' | 'PATCH';\n  path: string;\n  description: string;\n  auth?: 'none' | 'bearer' | 'mtls';\n}\n```\n\n#### `K8sResource` — Kubernetes CRD documentation block\n\n```tsx\ninterface K8sResourceProps {\n  group: string;\n  version: string;\n  kind: string;\n  scope: 'Namespaced' | 'Cluster';\n  yamlExample?: string;\n}\n```\n\n### 2.6 Version Metadata (`versions.json`)\n\n```json\n[\"current\", \"0.1.x\"]\n```\n\nManaged by `docusaurus docs:version 0.1.x` command. Each release creates a snapshot of the current docs.\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 Internal APIs (Docusaurus Plugin Contracts)\n\nDocusaurus does not expose external APIs; instead it defines plugin/preset contracts:\n\n| Contract | Type | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs` | Plugin | Processes `/docs/` markdown, builds sidebar, generates pages |\n| `@docusaurus/preset-classic` | Preset | Bundles docs, blog, pages, theme-classic |\n| `@docusaurus/theme-classic` | Theme | Provides default UI components (navbar, footer, sidebar) |\n\n### 3.2 External Integration Points\n\n| Integration | Configuration | Purpose |\n|-------------|---------------|---------|\n| Algolia DocSearch | `themeConfig.algolia` | Full-text search across docs |\n| GitHub Edit URL | `presets[0][1].docs.editUrl` | \"Edit this page\" links to GitHub |\n| GitHub Pages | `organizationName`, `projectName`, `deploymentBranch` | `npm run deploy` pushes to gh-pages |\n| Google Analytics | `themeConfig.algolia` or custom plugin | Usage analytics (optional) |\n\n### 3.3 Build Output Contract\n\n```\nbuild/\n├── index.html                    # Landing page\n├── docs/\n│   ├── intro/\n│   │   └── index.html\n│   ├── getting-started/\n│   │   ├── installation/\n│   │   ├── quick-start/\n│   │   └── configuration/\n│   ├── next/                     # \"current\" versioned docs\n│   │   └── ...\n│   └── version-0.1.x/\n│       └── ...\n├── zh/                           # Chinese locale\n│   └── docs/\n│       └── ...\n├── blog/\n│   └── ...\n├── assets/\n│   ├── js/\n│   ├── css/\n│   └── images/\n└── 404.html                      # Custom 404 page\n```\n\n### 3.4 URL Routing Contract\n\n| Pattern | Resolution |\n|---------|-----------|\n| `/docs/<id>` | Maps to `docs/<id>.md` |\n| `/docs/<version>/<id>` | Maps to `versioned_docs/version-<version>/<id>.md` |\n| `/<locale>/docs/<id>` | Maps to `i18n/<locale>/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/current/<id>.md` |\n| `/blog/<slug>` | Maps to `blog/<slug>.md` |\n| `/<path>` | Maps to `src/pages/<path>.tsx` or `src/pages/<path>/index.tsx` |\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Build-Time Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Handling |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| Missing sidebar reference | `sidebars.ts` references non-existent doc ID | Build fails with clear error: `Doc sidebar item \"x\" references a non-existent doc` |\n| Broken internal link | Markdown link to non-existent doc | Build warning (configurable to error via `onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'throw'`) |\n| Broken image reference | Image path does not exist | Build warning (configurable via `onBrokenAssets: 'throw'`) |\n| Invalid frontmatter | Malformed YAML frontmatter | Build fails with YAML parse error |\n| MDX syntax error | Invalid JSX in `.mdx` file | Build fails with JSX compilation error |\n| Duplicate doc ID | Two files with same inferred ID | Build fails with duplicate ID error |\n| Missing translation | i18n locale missing a translated doc | Falls back to default locale (English) with console warning |\n\n### 4.2 Runtime Errors (Client-Side)\n\n| Error | Cause | Handling |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| 404 page not found | User navigates to non-existent route | Custom 404 page with search and navigation links |\n| Search index unavailable | Algolia API key invalid or network error | Graceful degradation: search box shows \"Search unavailable\" |\n| Code block syntax error | Unsupported language in code fence | Prism falls back to plain text rendering |\n| Theme component error | Swizzled component throws error | React error boundary catches; shows fallback UI |\n\n### 4.3 CI/CD Errors\n\n| Error | Cause | Handling |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| `npm run build` fails | Build-time error (see 4.1) | CI fails; PR blocked from merging |\n| Deploy authentication failure | GitHub token missing or expired | CI fails; requires secret rotation |\n| Branch protection | gh-pages branch protected | CI fails; requires branch config change |\n\n### 4.4 Error Configuration\n\n```typescript\n// docusaurus.config.ts — strict mode for CI\nconst config: Config = {\n  onBrokenLinks: 'throw',       // Fail build on broken links\n  onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'warn', // Warn on broken markdown links\n  onBrokenAssets: 'throw',       // Fail build on missing images\n  onDuplicateRoutes: 'throw',    // Fail build on duplicate routes\n  // ...\n};\n```\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope | Tool | Frequency |\n|----------|-------|------|-----------|\n| Build validation | `npm run build` succeeds with no errors | Docusaurus CLI | Every PR |\n| Link checking | No broken internal/external links | `docusaurus-mdx-checker` or `check-links` | Every PR |\n| Visual regression | UI matches expected rendering | Playwright / Percy | On demand |\n| Accessibility | WCAG 2.1 AA compliance | axe-core, Lighthouse CI | Every PR |\n| Performance | Lighthouse scores ≥ 90 | Lighthouse CI | Every PR |\n| i18n completeness | All zh translations present | Custom script | Weekly |\n| SEO validation | Meta tags, Open Graph, structured data | Custom script | Every PR |\n\n### 5.2 Build Validation\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies\ncd docs && npm install\n\n# Type check\nnpx tsc --noEmit\n\n# Build (static site generation)\nnpm run build\n\n# Serve locally for manual verification\nnpm run serve\n```\n\n### 5.3 Link Checking\n\n```bash\n# Check for broken links in built output\nnpx check-links build/**/*.html\n\n# Docusaurus built-in broken link detection (during build)\n# Configured via onBrokenLinks: 'throw' in docusaurus.config.ts\n```\n\n### 5.4 Lighthouse CI Configuration\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ci\": {\n    \"collect\": {\n      \"staticDistDir\": \"./build\",\n      \"settings\": {\n        \"preset\": \"desktop\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"assert\": {\n      \"assertions\": {\n        \"categories:performance\": [\"warn\", { \"minScore\": 0.9 }],\n        \"categories:accessibility\": [\"error\", { \"minScore\": 0.95 }],\n        \"categories:best-practices\": [\"warn\", { \"minScore\": 0.9 }],\n        \"categories:seo\": [\"error\", { \"minScore\": 0.9 }]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 5.5 i18n Completeness Check\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# scripts/check-i18n.sh — compare en and zh doc file counts\nEN_COUNT=$(find docs/docs -name \"*.md\" -o -name \"*.mdx\" | wc -l)\nZH_COUNT=$(find docs/i18n/zh/docusaurus-plugin-content-docs/current -name \"*.md\" -o -name \"*.mdx\" | wc -l)\nCOVERAGE=$(echo \"scale=1; $ZH_COUNT * 100 / $EN_COUNT\" | bc)\necho \"Chinese translation coverage: ${COVERAGE}%\"\nif (( $(echo \"$COVERAGE < 80\" | bc -l) )); then\n  echo \"WARNING: Translation coverage below 80%\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n```\n\n### 5.6 Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Full test suite\ncd docs && npm run build && npm run check-links && npm run check-i18n\n\n# Development server with hot reload\ncd docs && npm start\n\n# Type checking\ncd docs && npx tsc --noEmit\n\n# Production build\ncd docs && NODE_ENV=production npm run build\n\n# Preview production build locally\ncd docs && npm run serve -- --build --port 3000\n```\n\n### 5.7 CI Pipeline for Docs\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/docs.yml\nname: Docs CI\n\non:\n  pull_request:\n    paths:\n      - 'docs/**'\n      - '.github/workflows/docs.yml'\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    defaults:\n      run:\n        working-directory: docs\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n        with:\n          node-version: '20'\n          cache: 'npm'\n          cache-dependency-path: docs/package-lock.json\n      - run: npm ci\n      - run: npx tsc --noEmit\n      - run: npm run build\n      - name: Check links\n        run: npx check-links build/**/*.html --timeout 10000\n      - name: Check i18n coverage\n        run: bash ../scripts/check-i18n.sh\n      - name: Upload build artifact\n        if: success()\n        uses: actions/upload-pages-artifact@v3\n        with:\n          path: docs/build\n\n  deploy:\n    needs: build\n    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      pages: write\n      id-token: write\n    environment:\n      name: github-pages\n      url: ${{ steps.deployment.outputs.page_url }}\n    steps:\n      - name: Deploy to GitHub Pages\n        id: deployment\n        uses: actions/deploy-pages@v4\n```\n\n### 5.8 Coverage Targets\n\n| Metric | Target |\n|--------|--------|\n| Build success rate | 100% |\n| Broken links | 0 |\n| i18n coverage (zh) | ≥ 80% |\n| Lighthouse Performance | ≥ 90 |\n| Lighthouse Accessibility | ≥ 95 |\n| Lighthouse SEO | ≥ 90 |\n| Lighthouse Best Practices | ≥ 90 |\n\n### 5.9 Risk Areas\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|\n| Docusaurus major version upgrade breaks config | Pin `^3.7.0` (minor updates only); test upgrade in separate branch |\n| Algolia DocSearch index not approved | Use `@easyops-cn/docusaurus-search-local` as fallback |\n| Large doc set causes slow builds | Use incremental builds; cache `node_modules` and `.docusaurus` |\n| Translation drift (en updated, zh stale) | Weekly i18n coverage check; automated Slack notification |\n| GitHub Pages rate limits | Use CDN (Cloudflare) in front of GitHub Pages for production |\n| MDX component breaking changes | Unit test custom components; pin React version |\n| Versioned docs diverge from current | Enforce `docusaurus docs:version` on each release tag |\n\n### 5.10 Initial Content Checklist\n\n| Doc | Status | Priority |\n|-----|--------|----------|\n| `intro.md` — Project overview | **Draft** | P0 |\n| `getting-started/installation.md` — Helm install guide | **Draft** | P0 |\n| `getting-started/quick-start.md` — 5-minute tutorial | **Draft** | P0 |\n| `getting-started/configuration.md` — Helm values reference | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `architecture/overview.md` — System architecture | **Draft** | P0 |\n| `architecture/components.md` — Component deep dive | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `architecture/session-routing.md` — Router + session management | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `architecture/sandbox-lifecycle.md` — Sandbox creation to cleanup | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `user-guide/code-interpreter.md` — Code Interpreter usage | **Draft** | P0 |\n| `user-guide/agent-runtime.md` — Agent Runtime usage | **Draft** | P0 |\n| `user-guide/cli.md` — CLI commands reference | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `user-guide/python-sdk.md` — Python SDK reference | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `api-reference/control-plane.md` — Workload Manager API | **Draft** | P2 |\n| `api-reference/data-plane.md` — Router API | **Draft** | P2 |\n| `api-reference/crds.md` — CRD reference | **Draft** | P2 |\n| `operations/deployment.md` — Production deployment guide | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `operations/monitoring.md` — Metrics and alerts | **Draft** | P2 |\n| `operations/troubleshooting.md` — Common issues | **Draft** | P1 |\n| `operations/security.md` — Auth, RBAC, network policies | **Draft** | P1 |\n\n## 6. Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Scaffold (Week 1)\n\n- [ ] Initialize Docusaurus project in `docs/` directory\n- [ ] Configure `docusaurus.config.ts` with AgentCube branding\n- [ ] Set up sidebar structure (`sidebars.ts`)\n- [ ] Create category directories with `_category_.json` files\n- [ ] Add custom CSS theme (`src/css/custom.css`)\n- [ ] Configure TypeScript (`tsconfig.json`)\n- [ ] Add Mermaid diagram support\n\n### Phase 2: Content Migration (Week 1-2)\n\n- [ ] Write `intro.md` from `project.md`\n- [ ] Migrate architecture docs from existing `design.md` files\n- [ ] Write getting-started guides (installation, quick-start)\n- [ ] Create user guide stubs for Code Interpreter, Agent Runtime, CLI, SDK\n- [ ] Add API reference skeletons\n\n### Phase 3: i18n Setup (Week 2)\n\n- [ ] Initialize Chinese locale (`docusaurus write-translations --locale zh`)\n- [ ] Translate intro and getting-started docs\n- [ ] Set up translation workflow documentation\n- [ ] Add i18n coverage check script\n\n### Phase 4: CI/CD (Week 2-3)\n\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/docs.yml`\n- [ ] Configure GitHub Pages deployment\n- [ ] Add Lighthouse CI checks\n- [ ] Add link checking to PR pipeline\n- [ ] Configure custom domain (optional)\n\n### Phase 5: Polish (Week 3)\n\n- [ ] Add custom MDX components (`ApiEndpoint`, `K8sResource`)\n- [ ] Configure Algolia DocSearch (apply for indexing)\n- [ ] Set up local search fallback\n- [ ] Add versioned docs for first release\n- [ ] Performance optimization (image compression, code splitting)\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/docs/design.md","time":{"start":1775898088170,"end":1775898088182}}}}
